  "support": "Two thin, isolated marble fragments, contiguous and composed in turn of reassembled elements: the first consists of four sections, the second of three. An upper marginal lacuna is visible, especially in the second fragment on the right. The piece appears to belong to an architrave, possibly constructed from separate panels, as the relatively clean-cut edge on the left might suggest. A moulding is partially preserved along the lower edge. The surface is smooth and carefully finished, with traces of lime and minor abrasions; the back is polished.",
